Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1}(peeled) into 1-inch-thick wedges; mince one wedge. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice lengthwise into long wedges. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add minced onion and @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}. Cook, stirring, until onion is softened and couscous is lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @water{3/4%cup} and @veggie stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

Meanwhile, toss zucchini and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, @sumac{1%teaspoon}, @salt{to taste}, and @pepper{to taste}.

Broil, tossing halfway through, until lightly charred, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

While veggies cook, slice @grilling cheese{6%ounce} into four large pieces.

Place @za'atar spice{1%tablespoon} on a #plate{}. Coat cheese in spice, pressing to adhere.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add cheese and cook until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

Transfer cooked couscous to a #large bowl{}. Stir in tomatoes, lemon zest, half the broiled veggies, half the cilantro, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous mixture between plates. Top with remaining broiled veggies and grilling cheese. Garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.